            "title": "HII Teams with GrayMatter Robotics to Integrate Physical AI into Manned and Unmanned Shipbuilding",
            "id": "fb97f43b-0dad-45d9-b6b8-f75b611c97e0",
            "description": "In Carson, California, on April 6, 2026, a memorandum of understanding (MOU) was signed between HII (NYSE: HII) and GrayMatter Robotics (GMR). The agreement aims to explore integrating GMR’s Physical AI technologies into shipbuilding operations to enhance efficiency. This collaboration could potentially accelerate throughput, fortify the maritime industrial sector, and supplement the shipbuilding workforce. The focus will be on introducing autonomous technologies for surface preparation, coating, and inspection in shipbuilding processes. The MOU was signed at GrayMatter Robotics’ headquarters and was attended by Eric Chewning, HII’s executive vice president of maritime systems and corporate strategy, and Ariyan Kabir, GrayMatter Robotics CEO and co-founder.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/fb97f43b-0dad-45d9-b6b8-f75b611c97e0",
